WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.473 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:01.473 --> 00:00:04.910 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.910 --> 00:00:08.347 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.347 --> 00:00:22.595 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.595 --> 00:00:24.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Have
you heard the phrase,

00:00:24.220 --> 00:00:28.150 align:middle line:84%
you can create your own reality,
or the law of attraction?

00:00:28.150 --> 00:00:31.360 align:middle line:84%
What does that really mean
on a quantum physics level?

00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:32.980 align:middle line:84%
As fast as the
world is changing,

00:00:32.980 --> 00:00:36.130 align:middle line:84%
wouldn't it be helpful to
learn new ways of thinking

00:00:36.130 --> 00:00:38.950 align:middle line:84%
and how to think
on a quantum level?

00:00:38.950 --> 00:00:41.440 align:middle line:84%
Joining me to break this
down in relatable terms

00:00:41.440 --> 00:00:44.040 align:middle line:90%
is physicist Dr. Fred Alan Wolf.

00:00:44.040 --> 00:00:46.420 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Quantum, as he's
affectionately called,

00:00:46.420 --> 00:00:50.110 align:middle line:84%
he has the unique ability to
communicate the complex topics

00:00:50.110 --> 00:00:53.590 align:middle line:84%
of quantum physics into
more understandable terms,

00:00:53.590 --> 00:00:56.110 align:middle line:84%
as he did with the movie
"What the Bleep Do We Know!?"

00:00:56.110 --> 00:00:56.470 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:00:56.470 --> 00:00:57.920 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for joining me.

00:00:57.920 --> 00:00:59.337 align:middle line:10%
>>FRED ALAN WOLF:
Thank you, Lisa.

00:00:59.337 --> 00:01:01.420 align:middle line:10%
It's a pleasure to
be on this show.

00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:02.220 align:middle line:10%
Your show.

00:01:02.220 --> 00:01:03.160 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGH]

00:01:03.160 --> 00:01:05.243 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I'm really
excited to have you here.

00:01:05.243 --> 00:01:07.750 align:middle line:10%
So can you tell us how
quantum physics can

00:01:07.750 --> 00:01:11.710 align:middle line:10%
help us understand the rapid
changes that we're experiencing

00:01:11.710 --> 00:01:12.792 align:middle line:10%
in the world today?

00:01:12.792 --> 00:01:14.500 align:middle line:10%
Help us cope with it
a little bit better.

00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:14.920 align:middle line:10%
>>WOLF: OK.

00:01:14.920 --> 00:01:16.060 align:middle line:10%
I'll try.

00:01:16.060 --> 00:01:19.960 align:middle line:84%
First of all, we have to try
to grasp, what is this thing

00:01:19.960 --> 00:01:21.372 align:middle line:90%
called quantum physics?

00:01:21.372 --> 00:01:23.830 align:middle line:84%
So if you don't mind, I'm going
to paint a kind of picture.

00:01:23.830 --> 00:01:26.530 align:middle line:84%
Tell you a little bit of a
story, if that's OK with you.

00:01:26.530 --> 00:01:27.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Please.

00:01:27.430 --> 00:01:28.420 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: All right.

00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:34.120 align:middle line:84%
In the beginning, when we
first came out of the caves

00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:39.850 align:middle line:84%
and the uga-boogas were all
around us, we needed something.

00:01:39.850 --> 00:01:41.550 align:middle line:90%
We were afraid.

00:01:41.550 --> 00:01:43.160 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we were going to be--

00:01:43.160 --> 00:01:43.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Survival.

00:01:43.960 --> 00:01:44.310 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:01:44.310 --> 00:01:45.110 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:01:45.110 --> 00:01:46.810 align:middle line:10%
So we started trying
to figure out,

00:01:46.810 --> 00:01:50.110 align:middle line:10%
what is this thing we're in,
this nature that we're in?

00:01:50.110 --> 00:01:53.590 align:middle line:10%
And as the years went by,
we began to see, well,

00:01:53.590 --> 00:01:55.070 align:middle line:10%
we can control fire.

00:01:55.070 --> 00:01:56.200 align:middle line:90%
We can control air.

00:01:56.200 --> 00:01:57.670 align:middle line:90%
We can control water.

00:01:57.670 --> 00:02:02.110 align:middle line:84%
We began to learn about the
nature of things by the things

00:02:02.110 --> 00:02:05.980 align:middle line:84%
that we could get our mitts
on, how we control them.

00:02:05.980 --> 00:02:10.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, now we're going to
jump thousands of years.

00:02:10.010 --> 00:02:10.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:02:10.810 --> 00:02:12.610 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And as we jump
thousands of years,

00:02:12.610 --> 00:02:16.480 align:middle line:84%
we get into a kind of
mechanical world view.

00:02:16.480 --> 00:02:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And this is a world
view in which everything

00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:23.040 align:middle line:90%
is viewed as being mechanical.

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:25.120 align:middle line:90%
Everything is a machine.

00:02:25.120 --> 00:02:26.910 align:middle line:84%
We have a little bit
of that even today,

00:02:26.910 --> 00:02:30.820 align:middle line:84%
in today's thinking, which I
don't necessarily subscribe to.

00:02:30.820 --> 00:02:33.280 align:middle line:84%
But nevertheless,
that was the thinking

00:02:33.280 --> 00:02:38.620 align:middle line:84%
during the time of Newton
and Galileo and Bruno,

00:02:38.620 --> 00:02:40.870 align:middle line:84%
and a number of
people who were around

00:02:40.870 --> 00:02:42.430 align:middle line:90%
during this period of time.

00:02:42.430 --> 00:02:43.840 align:middle line:90%
Descartes.

00:02:43.840 --> 00:02:44.990 align:middle line:90%
I won't get into all that.

00:02:44.990 --> 00:02:47.800 align:middle line:84%
But all I want to
get into with you

00:02:47.800 --> 00:02:50.980 align:middle line:84%
is the idea that since
everything was a machine,

00:02:50.980 --> 00:02:52.780 align:middle line:84%
we looked at things
mechanically.

00:02:52.780 --> 00:02:54.738 align:middle line:84%
And what do you
do with machines?

00:02:54.738 --> 00:02:56.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, you take them
apart, and you put them

00:02:56.530 --> 00:02:57.890 align:middle line:90%
back together again.

00:02:57.890 --> 00:02:59.860 align:middle line:84%
So the whole thing
is, can we take apart

00:02:59.860 --> 00:03:02.330 align:middle line:84%
the universe or the
things we have around us

00:03:02.330 --> 00:03:04.160 align:middle line:84%
and put them back
together again?

00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:05.770 align:middle line:90%
And the answer is, pretty well.

00:03:05.770 --> 00:03:10.490 align:middle line:84%
We did very well until about
the turn of the 20th century.

00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:13.480 align:middle line:84%
Then we began taking
things apart so well

00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:15.640 align:middle line:84%
that when we tried to put
them back together again,

00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:16.450 align:middle line:90%
they didn't fit.

00:03:16.450 --> 00:03:17.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:03:17.250 --> 00:03:18.920 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Nothing made any sense.

00:03:18.920 --> 00:03:22.780 align:middle line:84%
We needed a kind of
new physics, a new way

00:03:22.780 --> 00:03:25.360 align:middle line:84%
to bring things
back together again.

00:03:25.360 --> 00:03:28.583 align:middle line:84%
And that gave us
some way of thinking,

00:03:28.583 --> 00:03:29.500 align:middle line:90%
a new way of thinking.

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:31.493 align:middle line:84%
Well, what are we
actually trying

00:03:31.493 --> 00:03:32.660 align:middle line:90%
to build in the first place?

00:03:32.660 --> 00:03:34.870 align:middle line:84%
What are the things
we've taken apart?

00:03:34.870 --> 00:03:37.630 align:middle line:84%
What are the things we're trying
to put back together again?

00:03:37.630 --> 00:03:40.870 align:middle line:84%
And what arose from all
that was a picture of things

00:03:40.870 --> 00:03:45.340 align:middle line:84%
being atoms and molecules
and then electrons.

00:03:45.340 --> 00:03:50.240 align:middle line:84%
And then we began to even take
apart the nucleus of atoms.

00:03:50.240 --> 00:03:53.620 align:middle line:84%
And now we have pictures
of quarks and anti-quarks

00:03:53.620 --> 00:03:55.420 align:middle line:90%
and gluons.

00:03:55.420 --> 00:03:56.363 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:03:56.363 --> 00:03:56.736 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:03:56.736 --> 00:03:57.536 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing.

00:03:57.536 --> 00:03:59.590 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: We're so much
into thingyness, so much

00:03:59.590 --> 00:04:02.110 align:middle line:84%
into taking things apart,
so much into things

00:04:02.110 --> 00:04:04.690 align:middle line:90%
have to be really thingy.

00:04:04.690 --> 00:04:08.670 align:middle line:84%
But quantum physics keeps going
and waving its finger at us

00:04:08.670 --> 00:04:11.530 align:middle line:84%
to say, (SINGING) na,
na, na, na, na, na, you

00:04:11.530 --> 00:04:13.360 align:middle line:90%
don't have it right yet.

00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:16.300 align:middle line:84%
And that seems to be the
case, because it's not

00:04:16.300 --> 00:04:17.890 align:middle line:90%
a question of thingyness.

00:04:17.890 --> 00:04:20.847 align:middle line:90%
It's more a question of mind.

00:04:20.847 --> 00:04:22.930 align:middle line:84%
And we're beginning to see
what quantum physics is

00:04:22.930 --> 00:04:26.290 align:middle line:84%
telling us is that things
are not made of things.

00:04:26.290 --> 00:04:30.130 align:middle line:84%
They're made of what we
think they are made of.

00:04:30.130 --> 00:04:33.790 align:middle line:84%
In other words, what we
think things are made of,

00:04:33.790 --> 00:04:38.410 align:middle line:84%
trying to build a picture which
is consistent with what we more

00:04:38.410 --> 00:04:41.320 align:middle line:84%
or less think we
understand leads us

00:04:41.320 --> 00:04:46.090 align:middle line:84%
into the whole picture
of pictures of atoms

00:04:46.090 --> 00:04:47.750 align:middle line:90%
as being little marbles.

00:04:47.750 --> 00:04:48.550 align:middle line:90%
But they're not.

00:04:48.550 --> 00:04:50.008 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I like that
so much better,

00:04:50.008 --> 00:04:51.460 align:middle line:84%
because you say
you like machines

00:04:51.460 --> 00:04:53.410 align:middle line:84%
to take apart and put
back together again,

00:04:53.410 --> 00:04:54.675 align:middle line:90%
and scientists do that.

00:04:54.675 --> 00:04:56.050 align:middle line:84%
I'm the type of
person that wants

00:04:56.050 --> 00:04:57.350 align:middle line:90%
to push it and make it work.

00:04:57.350 --> 00:04:58.120 align:middle line:90%
I just want it to work.

00:04:58.120 --> 00:04:58.920 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:00.970 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the world's
like that, especially

00:05:00.970 --> 00:05:02.320 align:middle line:90%
now in this day and age.

00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:05.260 align:middle line:10%
So it's interesting, because
there's a combination of two.

00:05:05.260 --> 00:05:09.250 align:middle line:84%
Pushing it and make it work
is kind of the quantum.

00:05:09.250 --> 00:05:13.670 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, underlying
the technology of today,

00:05:13.670 --> 00:05:18.440 align:middle line:84%
including the filming
of this show--

00:05:18.440 --> 00:05:22.650 align:middle line:84%
but the word filming is no
longer the right word anymore.

00:05:22.650 --> 00:05:24.600 align:middle line:84%
Everything that's
been done is done

00:05:24.600 --> 00:05:27.840 align:middle line:84%
in terms of kind of
pictures that are really not

00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:31.020 align:middle line:90%
pictures or dots, pixels.

00:05:31.020 --> 00:05:35.760 align:middle line:84%
And we're getting into the whole
idea of quantum dots, quantum

00:05:35.760 --> 00:05:36.870 align:middle line:90%
pictures.

00:05:36.870 --> 00:05:40.710 align:middle line:84%
Everything has been pixelated
into small and small, small

00:05:40.710 --> 00:05:41.730 align:middle line:90%
and smaller things.

00:05:41.730 --> 00:05:45.900 align:middle line:84%
And again, we're dealing
with no longer thinking this

00:05:45.900 --> 00:05:50.730 align:middle line:84%
as much as we are with idea-like
substance, idea-like things.

00:05:50.730 --> 00:05:53.670 align:middle line:84%
They're not really things,
but idea-like things,

00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:59.250 align:middle line:84%
which turn into virtual
reality, television

00:05:59.250 --> 00:06:02.237 align:middle line:84%
shows right now where the
picture you see on the screen

00:06:02.237 --> 00:06:04.320 align:middle line:84%
is even brighter than the
picture you see when you

00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:05.830 align:middle line:90%
walk outside of your own house.

00:06:05.830 --> 00:06:06.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes

00:06:06.630 --> 00:06:09.600 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And it's just
amazing how we are

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:14.440 align:middle line:90%
into creating our own reality.

00:06:14.440 --> 00:06:17.310 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
quantum physics has led us.

00:06:17.310 --> 00:06:20.360 align:middle line:84%
As soon as we began to
realize what it was telling us

00:06:20.360 --> 00:06:23.940 align:middle line:84%
and we began to let go of
marbles and billiard balls

00:06:23.940 --> 00:06:27.000 align:middle line:84%
or whatever-- which are OK if
you're playing with marbles

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:27.970 align:middle line:90%
and billiard balls.

00:06:27.970 --> 00:06:31.650 align:middle line:84%
But while we're playing
with pictures and ideas

00:06:31.650 --> 00:06:36.750 align:middle line:84%
and intelligence and
artificial intelligence

00:06:36.750 --> 00:06:40.920 align:middle line:84%
and the kind of pixellation that
goes into making a television

00:06:40.920 --> 00:06:43.380 align:middle line:84%
show like this one,
we're no longer

00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:46.930 align:middle line:84%
dealing with marbles
and billiard balls.

00:06:46.930 --> 00:06:50.040 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
quantum comes into view,

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:52.530 align:middle line:84%
and this is what
makes your desire

00:06:52.530 --> 00:06:54.990 align:middle line:84%
to have it come
into view by pushing

00:06:54.990 --> 00:06:58.270 align:middle line:90%
that button become what it is.

00:06:58.270 --> 00:06:59.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Makes it happen.

00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:01.108 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: I mean, we're
all becoming like--

00:07:01.108 --> 00:07:02.107 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:07:02.107 --> 00:07:03.690 align:middle line:84%
This is a picture I
had the other day.

00:07:03.690 --> 00:07:05.130 align:middle line:90%
We're like blobs.

00:07:05.130 --> 00:07:08.310 align:middle line:84%
We're big blobs,
and we have a thumb.

00:07:08.310 --> 00:07:11.040 align:middle line:90%
And the thumb is on a screen.

00:07:11.040 --> 00:07:13.160 align:middle line:84%
We press the screen,
and the pictures appear,

00:07:13.160 --> 00:07:13.960 align:middle line:90%
and the blob goes--

00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:14.800 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING NONSENSE]

00:07:14.800 --> 00:07:15.600 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:16.350 align:middle line:90%
I like that.

00:07:16.350 --> 00:07:17.600 align:middle line:90%
And we press the button again.

00:07:17.600 --> 00:07:19.500 align:middle line:90%
Oh, now I don't like that.

00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:20.670 align:middle line:90%
I'll press the button again.

00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:23.115 align:middle line:84%
And everything is
changing because we're

00:07:23.115 --> 00:07:24.760 align:middle line:90%
controlling our reality.

00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:28.260 align:middle line:84%
So we're learning more and
more from our technology

00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:31.817 align:middle line:84%
what it means to
create our own reality.

00:07:31.817 --> 00:07:33.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is such great news.

00:07:33.150 --> 00:07:36.390 align:middle line:84%
This is such great news from a
physicist that what we're doing

00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:37.770 align:middle line:90%
is working now.

00:07:37.770 --> 00:07:39.900 align:middle line:84%
And we can work with
it more than ever.

00:07:39.900 --> 00:07:41.400 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And we're
just at the bottom

00:07:41.400 --> 00:07:45.030 align:middle line:84%
rung of what that means to
create your own reality.

00:07:45.030 --> 00:07:48.480 align:middle line:84%
Physicists could see it
happening in experiments

00:07:48.480 --> 00:07:50.560 align:middle line:84%
that they did, but
these were experiments.

00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:53.370 align:middle line:84%
These were very technical,
very difficult to explain

00:07:53.370 --> 00:07:54.880 align:middle line:90%
in a layman's term.

00:07:54.880 --> 00:07:57.430 align:middle line:84%
But basically, it
is the same thing.

00:07:57.430 --> 00:08:00.850 align:middle line:84%
It is creating your own reality,
and we saw it happening.

00:08:00.850 --> 00:08:03.140 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we no longer
have pictures--

00:08:03.140 --> 00:08:04.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, when we deal
with quantum physics,

00:08:04.890 --> 00:08:08.430 align:middle line:84%
we're not dealing, as I said
before, we're thingyness.

00:08:08.430 --> 00:08:12.050 align:middle line:84%
We're dealing with
idea-like things.

00:08:12.050 --> 00:08:13.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Concepts, right?

00:08:13.050 --> 00:08:13.310 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Concepts.

00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:13.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:13.970 --> 00:08:14.770 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Right.

00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:16.830 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So if you're
in a situation-- say

00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:18.390 align:middle line:10%
you're going down
a specific track

00:08:18.390 --> 00:08:20.880 align:middle line:10%
or there's things that are
happening in your life,

00:08:20.880 --> 00:08:24.630 align:middle line:10%
you don't necessarily like them,
can you use quantum physics

00:08:24.630 --> 00:08:29.160 align:middle line:10%
to really jump into
a different reality,

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:33.440 align:middle line:10%
to create on a different level,
and not create the same story

00:08:33.440 --> 00:08:34.260 align:middle line:10%
over and over?

00:08:34.260 --> 00:08:36.659 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: The thing
which is interesting is

00:08:36.659 --> 00:08:40.350 align:middle line:84%
that we are doing that, even
though we don't recognize

00:08:40.350 --> 00:08:42.840 align:middle line:90%
that we're doing that.

00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:46.650 align:middle line:84%
The thought or
the idea which has

00:08:46.650 --> 00:08:50.250 align:middle line:84%
you frozen in a
particular way of thinking

00:08:50.250 --> 00:08:54.990 align:middle line:84%
is being created,
recreated, recreated.

00:08:54.990 --> 00:08:58.030 align:middle line:84%
It becomes re-creation,
recreation.

00:08:58.030 --> 00:09:00.780 align:middle line:90%
It becomes your way of dealing.

00:09:00.780 --> 00:09:04.500 align:middle line:84%
And you're so much caught
in that circle or that web

00:09:04.500 --> 00:09:08.910 align:middle line:84%
of entanglement which keeps
you making the things appear

00:09:08.910 --> 00:09:12.930 align:middle line:84%
in the way that you feel
most comfortable with, even

00:09:12.930 --> 00:09:15.600 align:middle line:84%
though what you
call comfort for you

00:09:15.600 --> 00:09:18.645 align:middle line:90%
may be hell for somebody else.

00:09:18.645 --> 00:09:19.950 align:middle line:90%
We're constantly doing that.

00:09:19.950 --> 00:09:21.710 align:middle line:90%
And then we can work together.

00:09:21.710 --> 00:09:23.790 align:middle line:90%
We're not only just individuals.

00:09:23.790 --> 00:09:25.410 align:middle line:90%
We can share reality.

00:09:25.410 --> 00:09:30.370 align:middle line:84%
And each time we share reality,
the reality that I'm in

