00:17:06.520 --> 00:17:07.728 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Complementarity, yes.

00:17:07.728 --> 00:17:09.312 align:middle line:84%
Let me tell you a
little bit about it.

00:17:09.312 --> 00:17:10.400 align:middle line:90%
It's a wonderful concept.

00:17:10.400 --> 00:17:19.030 align:middle line:84%
The idea was that how and
what you choose to observe,

00:17:19.030 --> 00:17:23.380 align:middle line:84%
how you go about
making the observation,

00:17:23.380 --> 00:17:26.230 align:middle line:84%
quantum physics has
shown us that when

00:17:26.230 --> 00:17:30.130 align:middle line:84%
we go about making
an observation,

00:17:30.130 --> 00:17:33.880 align:middle line:84%
the way we choose to
make that observation

00:17:33.880 --> 00:17:40.030 align:middle line:84%
creates a reality for us at
that moment, which is cut off,

00:17:40.030 --> 00:17:43.000 align:middle line:84%
chopped off from all of
reality, other than just

00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:46.960 align:middle line:84%
that particular
moment of observation.

00:17:46.960 --> 00:17:50.620 align:middle line:84%
If we decided to
do that observation

00:17:50.620 --> 00:17:55.990 align:middle line:84%
from a different perspective,
not trying to pin it down, not

00:17:55.990 --> 00:18:02.640 align:middle line:84%
make it into thing, but make it
into something complementarity

00:18:02.640 --> 00:18:06.580 align:middle line:84%
to thingness, which would
be compassion, for example,

00:18:06.580 --> 00:18:09.910 align:middle line:84%
then we go into
that mode of seeing.

00:18:09.910 --> 00:18:12.190 align:middle line:84%
And once we're in
that mode of seeing,

00:18:12.190 --> 00:18:17.390 align:middle line:84%
the choppiness into particleness
or into little objects

00:18:17.390 --> 00:18:19.240 align:middle line:90%
is no longer present.

00:18:19.240 --> 00:18:23.980 align:middle line:84%
They're complementary to each
other, wave and particle.

00:18:23.980 --> 00:18:26.230 align:middle line:84%
Get on the wave, you're
not on the particle.

00:18:26.230 --> 00:18:29.240 align:middle line:84%
Get on the particle,
you've lost the wave.

00:18:29.240 --> 00:18:31.510 align:middle line:84%
So that's the whole idea
of what the principle

00:18:31.510 --> 00:18:34.160 align:middle line:84%
of complementarity
is really all about.

00:18:34.160 --> 00:18:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And it seems to exist
in many, many places.

00:18:39.700 --> 00:18:42.560 align:middle line:90%
It's in our thinking.

00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:46.990 align:middle line:84%
We more or less intuitively know
what things are complementary

00:18:46.990 --> 00:18:49.615 align:middle line:90%
and what things are not.

00:18:49.615 --> 00:18:52.790 align:middle line:84%
Jungian psychology was one
of the first to develop,

00:18:52.790 --> 00:18:54.970 align:middle line:84%
I think, a way of
thinking about that

00:18:54.970 --> 00:18:57.240 align:middle line:90%
in terms of Jungian functions.

00:18:57.240 --> 00:18:59.415 align:middle line:84%
This is psychological
talk, I know, but we can--

00:18:59.415 --> 00:19:00.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What do
you mean by that?

00:19:00.790 --> 00:19:02.095 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: I'll get into that.

