their way through it.

00:19:56.150 --> 00:19:57.463 align:middle line:90%
They're feelers.

00:19:57.463 --> 00:19:58.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Doesn't
really matter what

00:19:58.880 --> 00:20:01.047 align:middle line:84%
it's made of, as long as
you have a good time on it.

00:20:01.047 --> 00:20:04.130 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So sometimes
we've isolated and called

00:20:04.130 --> 00:20:06.860 align:middle line:84%
that the feminine versus
masculine point of view.

00:20:06.860 --> 00:20:09.530 align:middle line:84%
But today, there
are plenty of women

00:20:09.530 --> 00:20:13.490 align:middle line:84%
that are quite adept
at sensing and thinking

00:20:13.490 --> 00:20:17.300 align:middle line:84%
and quite a few men that
are feeling intuitives.

00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the things have
kind of switched around.

00:20:19.310 --> 00:20:23.000 align:middle line:84%
So it's not a question of sex
that determines these things.

00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:26.600 align:middle line:84%
It's a question of choice
and how one behaves.

00:20:26.600 --> 00:20:28.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I would even
say that there are

00:20:28.670 --> 00:20:30.770 align:middle line:90%
many of us that have all four.

00:20:30.770 --> 00:20:32.040 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: There are.

00:20:32.040 --> 00:20:33.950 align:middle line:84%
But the interesting
thing about them

00:20:33.950 --> 00:20:37.190 align:middle line:84%
is that they are in
complementary pairs.

00:20:37.190 --> 00:20:42.800 align:middle line:84%
You can more or less feel
and intuit at the same time,

00:20:42.800 --> 00:20:46.710 align:middle line:84%
but you can't feel and
think at the same time.

00:20:46.710 --> 00:20:50.030 align:middle line:84%
You could try, but the
minute you start thinking,

00:20:50.030 --> 00:20:51.275 align:middle line:90%
your feelings go out.

00:20:51.275 --> 00:20:53.670 align:middle line:84%
I use the analogy
of making love.

00:20:53.670 --> 00:20:55.920 align:middle line:84%
You're making love and you're
having a wonderful time.

00:20:55.920 --> 00:20:58.930 align:middle line:84%
The feelings are whatever,
senses and feeling.

00:20:58.930 --> 00:21:01.430 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly you think about,
oh, this is a wonderful thing.

00:21:01.430 --> 00:21:02.230 align:middle line:90%
[GASP]

00:21:02.230 --> 00:21:05.060 align:middle line:84%
And it suddenly stops because
you put it into thought.

00:21:05.060 --> 00:21:07.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That happens with
intuition and meditation.

00:21:07.420 --> 00:21:09.920 align:middle line:84%
You can go have a great journey,
and then all of the sudden,

00:21:09.920 --> 00:21:11.240 align:middle line:84%
you're aware of
the body and you--

00:21:11.240 --> 00:21:11.920 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Exactly.

00:21:11.920 --> 00:21:12.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --get sucked back.

00:21:12.650 --> 00:21:13.460 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Exactly.

00:21:13.460 --> 00:21:14.390 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:21:14.390 --> 00:21:18.150 align:middle line:84%
This is the complementarity
that we are used to.

00:21:18.150 --> 00:21:18.950 align:middle line:90%
We're used to it.

00:21:18.950 --> 00:21:22.040 align:middle line:84%
In fact, that's where
these old cliches

00:21:22.040 --> 00:21:25.370 align:middle line:84%
about feeling and intuiting
versus sensing and thinking

00:21:25.370 --> 00:21:26.880 align:middle line:90%
began to develop.

00:21:26.880 --> 00:21:29.510 align:middle line:84%
So we're used to the
concept of complementarity.

00:21:29.510 --> 00:21:34.160 align:middle line:84%
And now we find that it's not
only true for the way the mind

00:21:34.160 --> 00:21:35.750 align:middle line:84%
and the body work,
but it also is

00:21:35.750 --> 00:21:38.690 align:middle line:90%
true for principles of physics.

00:21:38.690 --> 00:21:40.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's really
about the observer,

00:21:40.850 --> 00:21:44.390 align:middle line:84%
and it's about perspectives,
again, I'm going to say.

00:21:44.390 --> 00:21:45.920 align:middle line:84%
But perspectives
isn't a word that's

00:21:45.920 --> 00:21:48.140 align:middle line:84%
used a lot in quantum
physics, is it?

00:21:48.140 --> 00:21:50.300 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, it is
in a certain sense.

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:52.475 align:middle line:90%
It's what you bring to bear.

00:21:52.475 --> 00:21:56.990 align:middle line:84%
The perspective you take depends
on how you go about looking.

00:21:56.990 --> 00:22:01.370 align:middle line:10%
So how you decide to look at
that particular whatever, how

00:22:01.370 --> 00:22:05.820 align:middle line:10%
you choose to observe
is called a perspective.

00:22:05.820 --> 00:22:09.440 align:middle line:10%
And you can imagine
up a picture where

00:22:09.440 --> 00:22:12.150 align:middle line:10%
you're looking up
at a structure,

00:22:12.150 --> 00:22:14.460 align:middle line:10%
and it looks a certain way.

00:22:14.460 --> 00:22:16.460 align:middle line:84%
From another point of
view, you're looking down,

00:22:16.460 --> 00:22:18.240 align:middle line:90%
it looks very different.

00:22:18.240 --> 00:22:21.120 align:middle line:84%
So these are different
perspectives.

00:22:21.120 --> 00:22:25.910 align:middle line:84%
And if you're looking, say,
from above like in a city,

00:22:25.910 --> 00:22:28.280 align:middle line:84%
looking down at a
big city, you're

00:22:28.280 --> 00:22:30.590 align:middle line:84%
getting a perspective
of the whole.

00:22:30.590 --> 00:22:33.320 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, the
individuals that you see

00:22:33.320 --> 00:22:34.445 align:middle line:90%
look more like ants to you.

00:22:34.445 --> 00:22:35.245 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:22:35.245 --> 00:22:36.745 align:middle line:84%
Like from an
airplane's perspective.

00:22:36.745 --> 00:22:38.328 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's do this
little experiment.

00:22:38.328 --> 00:22:39.830 align:middle line:84%
So you have this
great slide here

00:22:39.830 --> 00:22:41.790 align:middle line:84%
that shows us
different perspectives.

00:22:41.790 --> 00:22:42.590 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: OK.

00:22:42.590 --> 00:22:43.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And I love this.

00:22:43.180 --> 00:22:44.413 align:middle line:90%
Can you explain this to us?

00:22:44.413 --> 00:22:45.830 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: What you
see on the screen

00:22:45.830 --> 00:22:50.480 align:middle line:84%
before you is what
you might call a box.

00:22:50.480 --> 00:22:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And you can see there are
two definite square faces

00:22:54.410 --> 00:22:55.580 align:middle line:90%
to the box.

00:22:55.580 --> 00:22:59.780 align:middle line:10%
There's a square face which
you might say is in front,

00:22:59.780 --> 00:23:02.540 align:middle line:10%
and a square face which you
might say is in the rear.

00:23:02.540 --> 00:23:04.040 align:middle line:10%
Or you might look
at it another way.

00:23:04.040 --> 00:23:07.460 align:middle line:10%
There's a square face which
is lower than the square face

00:23:07.460 --> 00:23:09.170 align:middle line:10%
which is a little bit higher.

00:23:09.170 --> 00:23:11.480 align:middle line:10%
But look at that
box for a while.

00:23:11.480 --> 00:23:13.850 align:middle line:10%
Let your mind sink
into it for a while,

00:23:13.850 --> 00:23:16.610 align:middle line:10%
and then try to decide
which of those square faces

00:23:16.610 --> 00:23:19.220 align:middle line:10%
is actually in
front of the other.

00:23:19.220 --> 00:23:22.490 align:middle line:10%
Is it the lower one in front
or the upper one in front?

00:23:22.490 --> 00:23:25.730 align:middle line:10%
And for some people who are--

00:23:25.730 --> 00:23:29.120 align:middle line:10%
I would call them more
sensing, thinker types--

00:23:29.120 --> 00:23:33.050 align:middle line:10%
it gets frozen one way or the
other, and doesn't ever change.

00:23:33.050 --> 00:23:36.880 align:middle line:84%
But for intuitive feeling
types, it starts to jump.

00:23:36.880 --> 00:23:38.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's fluid.

00:23:38.120 --> 00:23:39.200 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: It jumps.

00:23:39.200 --> 00:23:42.260 align:middle line:84%
It actually goes, dap,
dap, dap, dap, dap, dap.

00:23:42.260 --> 00:23:45.600 align:middle line:84%
And if you watch that, if you're
watching it on home right now,

00:23:45.600 --> 00:23:47.360 align:middle line:84%
if you're watching
it right now, you

00:23:47.360 --> 00:23:49.648 align:middle line:84%
can find out what you are
by watching that picture

00:23:49.648 --> 00:23:50.940 align:middle line:90%
and seeing what happens to you.

00:23:50.940 --> 00:23:51.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, that's great.

00:23:51.590 --> 00:23:52.390 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:23:52.390 --> 00:23:54.515 align:middle line:10%
I see the box fluid, coming
in and out, in and out.

00:23:54.515 --> 00:23:55.315 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yeah.

00:23:55.315 --> 00:23:56.130 align:middle line:90%
In and out.

00:23:56.130 --> 00:23:58.640 align:middle line:90%
Fluid is more or less a flow.

00:23:58.640 --> 00:23:59.810 align:middle line:90%
This is pop!

00:23:59.810 --> 00:24:00.610 align:middle line:90%
Pop!

00:24:00.610 --> 00:24:01.410 align:middle line:90%
Pop!

00:24:01.410 --> 00:24:03.050 align:middle line:90%
It's quantum leap.

00:24:03.050 --> 00:24:04.310 align:middle line:90%
It's a jump.

00:24:04.310 --> 00:24:05.930 align:middle line:90%
It's like pixelated.

00:24:05.930 --> 00:24:07.550 align:middle line:90%
It's like quantum dots.

00:24:07.550 --> 00:24:09.290 align:middle line:90%
It's digitized.

00:24:09.290 --> 00:24:11.660 align:middle line:90%
It's not smooth, flowing.

00:24:11.660 --> 00:24:12.860 align:middle line:90%
Pop, pop, pop, pop, pop.

00:24:12.860 --> 00:24:14.670 align:middle line:90%
It's pop, pop, pop, pop, pop.

00:24:14.670 --> 00:24:16.770 align:middle line:90%
I call them pops, quantum pops.

00:24:16.770 --> 00:24:17.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's great.

00:24:17.740 --> 00:24:18.540 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:24:18.540 --> 00:24:20.710 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And that's
what you're observing.

00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:25.110 align:middle line:84%
Now the thing is, let's
say that you are seeing it

00:24:25.110 --> 00:24:27.480 align:middle line:90%
as a popping cube.

00:24:27.480 --> 00:24:30.870 align:middle line:84%
You're witnessing what would
be called a visual presentation

00:24:30.870 --> 00:24:32.470 align:middle line:90%
of a quantum leap.

00:24:32.470 --> 00:24:33.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:24:33.270 --> 00:24:33.510 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:24:33.510 --> 00:24:35.850 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: This is what a
quantum leap is all about.

00:24:35.850 --> 00:24:37.980 align:middle line:84%
Now there's another
way of seeing this.

00:24:37.980 --> 00:24:39.740 align:middle line:84%
Let's just go to
a pure red screen.

00:24:39.740 --> 00:24:40.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:24:40.540 --> 00:24:41.340 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: OK.

00:24:41.340 --> 00:24:43.500 align:middle line:90%
Now we're looking just red, OK?

00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:47.490 align:middle line:84%
Now suddenly we see
a blue square, OK?

00:24:47.490 --> 00:24:49.800 align:middle line:84%
Focus your mind on
that blue square.

00:24:49.800 --> 00:24:52.800 align:middle line:90%
Now a blue trapezoid appears.

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:56.910 align:middle line:84%
Maybe another blue trapezoid,
and then a third one,

00:24:56.910 --> 00:24:58.170 align:middle line:90%
and then a fourth one.

00:24:58.170 --> 00:25:01.650 align:middle line:84%
And now we have a
bunch of trapezoids

00:25:01.650 --> 00:25:04.240 align:middle line:90%
surrounding a square.

00:25:04.240 --> 00:25:08.820 align:middle line:84%
Focus your mind on all of those
as we change the background

00:25:08.820 --> 00:25:11.550 align:middle line:84%
from red to blue, but
only keep your mind

00:25:11.550 --> 00:25:14.850 align:middle line:84%
on the actual
geometrical flat figures

00:25:14.850 --> 00:25:16.630 align:middle line:90%
that I mentioned to you before.

00:25:16.630 --> 00:25:18.090 align:middle line:84%
And now even though
the background

00:25:18.090 --> 00:25:20.310 align:middle line:84%
may have changed
blue, you're still

00:25:20.310 --> 00:25:24.720 align:middle line:84%
focusing on just
those flat pieces.

00:25:24.720 --> 00:25:26.220 align:middle line:90%
There is no jumping.

00:25:26.220 --> 00:25:29.280 align:middle line:84%
You're now in the
complementary space.

00:25:29.280 --> 00:25:35.340 align:middle line:84%
All you're seeing is flat pieces
pasted with a kind of red halo

00:25:35.340 --> 00:25:36.750 align:middle line:90%
glowing around it.

00:25:36.750 --> 00:25:39.270 align:middle line:90%
Just focus on it that way.

00:25:39.270 --> 00:25:45.470 align:middle line:84%
And then when you're ready,
just say to yourself, jump.

00:25:45.470 --> 00:25:47.580 align:middle line:84%
And the minute you
say jump, suddenly

00:25:47.580 --> 00:25:49.110 align:middle line:90%
it changes back into a cube.

00:25:49.110 --> 00:25:52.563 align:middle line:84%
And there it is doing its
jumping back and forth.

00:25:52.563 --> 00:25:54.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So this is how
we can do this in life.

00:25:54.480 --> 00:25:57.190 align:middle line:84%
We can change our
perspectives that fast.

00:25:57.190 --> 00:25:58.600 align:middle line:90%
This is so important.

00:25:58.600 --> 00:26:00.720 align:middle line:10%
It's important for shifting
into different states

00:26:00.720 --> 00:26:04.530 align:middle line:10%
of being, knowledge,
parallel universes,

00:26:04.530 --> 00:26:07.200 align:middle line:10%
creating, creating
our own reality,

00:26:07.200 --> 00:26:08.760 align:middle line:10%
law of attraction, all of that.

00:26:08.760 --> 00:26:10.440 align:middle line:84%
This is the quantum
physics of it.

00:26:10.440 --> 00:26:11.240 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yeah.

00:26:11.240 --> 00:26:14.790 align:middle line:84%
It's a question of focusing
in or unfocusing and looking

00:26:14.790 --> 00:26:16.140 align:middle line:90%
at the whole picture.

00:26:16.140 --> 00:26:18.180 align:middle line:90%
And those are complementary.

00:26:18.180 --> 00:26:19.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:26:19.140 --> 00:26:20.890 align:middle line:84%
So you can look
at any situation,

00:26:20.890 --> 00:26:25.590 align:middle line:84%
and you can see a quantum
jump from that situation.

00:26:25.590 --> 00:26:28.680 align:middle line:84%
How does this work with
parallel realities?

00:26:28.680 --> 00:26:31.740 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, that's
a very good question.

00:26:31.740 --> 00:26:36.780 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at our
cube again, OK?

00:26:36.780 --> 00:26:42.390 align:middle line:84%
The notion that
there's a quantum leap

00:26:42.390 --> 00:26:48.420 align:middle line:84%
can be looked at as me saying
that in parallel worlds,

00:26:48.420 --> 00:26:51.540 align:middle line:84%
there are really
two perspectives.

00:26:51.540 --> 00:26:54.930 align:middle line:84%
And when you quantum
leap, in a sense,

00:26:54.930 --> 00:26:59.610 align:middle line:84%
you're kind of jumping from one
world into a parallel world.

00:26:59.610 --> 00:27:02.010 align:middle line:84%
But you're going with
it, so you don't really

00:27:02.010 --> 00:27:03.870 align:middle line:84%
notice that anything
has changed,

00:27:03.870 --> 00:27:06.030 align:middle line:84%
because more or less,
everything else around you

00:27:06.030 --> 00:27:08.080 align:middle line:90%
has kind of stayed the same.

00:27:08.080 --> 00:27:12.310 align:middle line:84%
So we're looking at that
from a point of view.

00:27:12.310 --> 00:27:14.730 align:middle line:84%
Now you can merge
the parallel worlds

00:27:14.730 --> 00:27:20.040 align:middle line:84%
when you see just the blue
pieces on the red background.

00:27:20.040 --> 00:27:22.320 align:middle line:84%
Now you're looking at the
parallel worlds merged.

00:27:22.320 --> 00:27:24.550 align:middle line:90%
But the minute you go into--

00:27:24.550 --> 00:27:25.530 align:middle line:90%
your jumping.

00:27:25.530 --> 00:27:30.180 align:middle line:84%
And every time you take
an option to choose

00:27:30.180 --> 00:27:34.560 align:middle line:84%
one or the other or have one
or the other appear before you,

00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:37.740 align:middle line:84%
you've entered into
a parallel reality.

00:27:37.740 --> 00:27:40.680 align:middle line:84%
And we do this so much
that we don't even

00:27:40.680 --> 00:27:43.180 align:middle line:84%
think of it in terms
of parallel realities.

00:27:43.180 --> 00:27:45.030 align:middle line:84%
But quantum physics
has indicated to us

00:27:45.030 --> 00:27:50.520 align:middle line:84%
that that is a way of
looking at what's going on.

00:27:50.520 --> 00:27:52.920 align:middle line:84%
It's just another
way of looking.

00:27:52.920 --> 00:27:56.140 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to necessarily
look at it that way,

00:27:56.140 --> 00:27:59.430 align:middle line:84%
but it may be
helpful to understand

00:27:59.430 --> 00:28:02.640 align:middle line:84%
that each of us by
the choices we make

00:28:02.640 --> 00:28:07.170 align:middle line:84%
enter into our own realities
parallel with others

00:28:07.170 --> 00:28:10.860 align:middle line:84%
where there's some agreement
as to what we can agree on.

00:28:10.860 --> 00:28:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And we may be able to
understand why there's

00:28:13.140 --> 00:28:15.930 align:middle line:84%
so much disagreement
when we understand

00:28:15.930 --> 00:28:20.165 align:middle line:84%
that we are looking at things
from different perspectives.

00:28:20.165 --> 00:28:21.540 align:middle line:84%
Different universes,
practically.

00:28:21.540 --> 00:28:22.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Universes.

00:28:22.340 --> 00:28:24.717 align:middle line:84%
And there's an infinite
amount of them, right?

00:28:24.717 --> 00:28:25.800 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: There's no ending.

00:28:25.800 --> 00:28:27.217 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's the
important part.

00:28:27.217 --> 00:28:30.120 align:middle line:84%
So if there's an infinite
amount of parallel universes,

00:28:30.120 --> 00:28:32.730 align:middle line:84%
you and I could have a
conversation right here, right

00:28:32.730 --> 00:28:36.360 align:middle line:84%
now, and then we can,
in a parallel universe,

00:28:36.360 --> 00:28:39.030 align:middle line:84%
make a different choice,
a different decision,

00:28:39.030 --> 00:28:41.280 align:middle line:84%
and we will continue on
a different decision.

00:28:41.280 --> 00:28:43.530 align:middle line:84%
Say we decide to get
up and leave right now.

00:28:43.530 --> 00:28:45.535 align:middle line:84%
Yet there could
be this interview

00:28:45.535 --> 00:28:47.160 align:middle line:84%
still happening in
a different reality?

00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:48.810 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:28:48.810 --> 00:28:50.490 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Well--

00:28:50.490 --> 00:28:51.660 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:28:51.660 --> 00:28:56.730 align:middle line:84%
--it's true, but the question
of how close those realities are

00:28:56.730 --> 00:29:02.550 align:middle line:84%
to each other is so vast that
in each reality, the one where

00:29:02.550 --> 00:29:04.620 align:middle line:84%
we separated from
each other, would

00:29:04.620 --> 00:29:06.930 align:middle line:84%
be so distinct from the
ones where we're still

00:29:06.930 --> 00:29:11.310 align:middle line:84%
in conversation that we would
not notice that we left,

00:29:11.310 --> 00:29:13.200 align:middle line:90%
that we had the other option.

00:29:13.200 --> 00:29:15.820 align:middle line:84%
Once that option is made
on such a grand scale

00:29:15.820 --> 00:29:19.060 align:middle line:84%
as the scale of having
this show and doing

