00:30:43.600 --> 00:30:45.470 align:middle line:84%
Just imagine that
you could see that.

00:30:45.470 --> 00:30:46.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:30:46.270 --> 00:30:50.060 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Now imagine,
if you will,

00:30:50.060 --> 00:30:54.070 align:middle line:84%
that you are able
to communicate what

00:30:54.070 --> 00:30:59.320 align:middle line:84%
you see to each of
your other alter egos

00:30:59.320 --> 00:31:01.330 align:middle line:90%
in each of the parallel worlds.

00:31:01.330 --> 00:31:05.320 align:middle line:84%
So in the world where you're
seeing lower face in front,

00:31:05.320 --> 00:31:08.890 align:middle line:90%
you're telling yourself, hey.

00:31:08.890 --> 00:31:12.280 align:middle line:84%
There's another viewpoint
that's also being seen.

00:31:12.280 --> 00:31:13.750 align:middle line:90%
I want you to know that.

00:31:13.750 --> 00:31:15.080 align:middle line:90%
Oh, really?

00:31:15.080 --> 00:31:15.880 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:31:15.880 --> 00:31:17.290 align:middle line:90%
There's another world.

00:31:17.290 --> 00:31:19.150 align:middle line:84%
Oh, there's another
way of looking at this.

00:31:19.150 --> 00:31:20.170 align:middle line:90%
Hey, wait a minute.

00:31:20.170 --> 00:31:21.910 align:middle line:90%
Maybe I can change.

00:31:21.910 --> 00:31:23.960 align:middle line:90%
And you do that in both worlds.

00:31:23.960 --> 00:31:26.110 align:middle line:84%
So in the quantum
physics experiment,

00:31:26.110 --> 00:31:29.560 align:middle line:84%
we do something similar
to what I just described

00:31:29.560 --> 00:31:32.230 align:middle line:90%
with atoms or molecules.

00:31:32.230 --> 00:31:34.120 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's more tricky.

00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:37.990 align:middle line:84%
Actually, we do it with what I
call qubits, quantum computers.

00:31:37.990 --> 00:31:40.540 align:middle line:84%
And it's very difficult--
it's more technical

00:31:40.540 --> 00:31:42.160 align:middle line:90%
than I think we can get into.

00:31:42.160 --> 00:31:45.190 align:middle line:84%
But basically, it's that
idea of communicating

00:31:45.190 --> 00:31:48.670 align:middle line:84%
what is seen from the outside
to the individuals that are

00:31:48.670 --> 00:31:50.770 align:middle line:90%
in the inside points of view.

00:31:50.770 --> 00:31:52.690 align:middle line:84%
And that way, they
have a memory,

00:31:52.690 --> 00:31:56.770 align:middle line:84%
a memory of what is possible,
even though for them it's

00:31:56.770 --> 00:31:57.980 align:middle line:90%
not possible.

00:31:57.980 --> 00:31:59.360 align:middle line:90%
They don't think it's possible.

00:31:59.360 --> 00:32:00.940 align:middle line:84%
But now they know
it is possible,

00:32:00.940 --> 00:32:02.770 align:middle line:84%
because another
point of view exists.

00:32:02.770 --> 00:32:04.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's been introduced.

00:32:04.030 --> 00:32:05.530 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And that's
something we have

00:32:05.530 --> 00:32:07.197 align:middle line:84%
to do in the reality
we're in right now.

00:32:07.197 --> 00:32:07.997 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:32:07.997 --> 00:32:10.240 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Even though we
don't see it as possible,

00:32:10.240 --> 00:32:12.580 align:middle line:84%
we have to-- that's what
I mean about compassion.

00:32:12.580 --> 00:32:16.420 align:middle line:84%
You begin to open up yourself
to the other point of view that

00:32:16.420 --> 00:32:20.000 align:middle line:84%
is possible, even though you
don't have that view right now.

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:21.760 align:middle line:84%
There's another
voice telling you,

00:32:21.760 --> 00:32:22.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's possible.

00:32:22.700 --> 00:32:23.500 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:32:23.500 --> 00:32:24.640 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: It's possible.

00:32:24.640 --> 00:32:27.220 align:middle line:84%
And this means that
the idea of you

00:32:27.220 --> 00:32:30.490 align:middle line:84%
being just you has to
dissolve into there

00:32:30.490 --> 00:32:34.750 align:middle line:84%
is no such thing as just
a single I. Every I is

00:32:34.750 --> 00:32:37.200 align:middle line:90%
the same I in each of us.

00:32:37.200 --> 00:32:38.975 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's complementarity.

00:32:38.975 --> 00:32:39.850 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: That's right.

00:32:39.850 --> 00:32:41.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So I love this,
because you have the quantum

00:32:41.770 --> 00:32:43.353 align:middle line:84%
perspective, and I'm
going to bring it

00:32:43.353 --> 00:32:46.130 align:middle line:90%
to a life kind of example.

00:32:46.130 --> 00:32:49.150 align:middle line:84%
So say, for example, you're
in one financial bracket,

00:32:49.150 --> 00:32:52.060 align:middle line:84%
and you know that there's a
possibility to make more money.

00:32:52.060 --> 00:32:53.620 align:middle line:84%
You see people
making more money.

00:32:53.620 --> 00:32:54.970 align:middle line:90%
You see successful people.

00:32:54.970 --> 00:32:57.820 align:middle line:84%
But you have this
reality that you are not,

00:32:57.820 --> 00:33:00.550 align:middle line:84%
and you can't pay your bills,
and you can't pay your rent.

00:33:00.550 --> 00:33:03.340 align:middle line:84%
You can go into
a quantum reality

00:33:03.340 --> 00:33:07.930 align:middle line:84%
where that exists, where you
are in that space of having

00:33:07.930 --> 00:33:10.420 align:middle line:84%
everything that you want and
being comfortable and being

00:33:10.420 --> 00:33:13.870 align:middle line:84%
taken care of and having that
financial abundance that you

00:33:13.870 --> 00:33:15.400 align:middle line:90%
desire.

00:33:15.400 --> 00:33:18.790 align:middle line:84%
And you can constantly
overlap that

00:33:18.790 --> 00:33:22.160 align:middle line:84%
and overlap, and really
share that reality.

00:33:22.160 --> 00:33:24.400 align:middle line:84%
But what happens when
the judgment comes in?

00:33:24.400 --> 00:33:25.450 align:middle line:90%
What does that do?

00:33:25.450 --> 00:33:26.693 align:middle line:90%
What does the judgment do?

00:33:26.693 --> 00:33:28.360 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, let's
explain a little bit

00:33:28.360 --> 00:33:30.220 align:middle line:90%
about what we call judgment.

00:33:30.220 --> 00:33:34.450 align:middle line:84%
Judgment is really a
voice which is telling us,

00:33:34.450 --> 00:33:36.560 align:middle line:90%
you can't have that.

00:33:36.560 --> 00:33:40.960 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of a negation of
the dream kind of thing.

00:33:40.960 --> 00:33:44.770 align:middle line:84%
And the point is that
quantum physics gives us

00:33:44.770 --> 00:33:47.350 align:middle line:84%
not only the perspective
of, we can have something.

00:33:47.350 --> 00:33:51.190 align:middle line:84%
It also gives us the perspective
that we can't have something.

00:33:51.190 --> 00:33:55.690 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it's not
only one thing or the other.

00:33:55.690 --> 00:33:59.020 align:middle line:84%
It's both and rather
than either or.

00:33:59.020 --> 00:34:02.920 align:middle line:84%
So you deal with it
as you would deal

00:34:02.920 --> 00:34:06.080 align:middle line:84%
with any particular thought
process that you have.

00:34:06.080 --> 00:34:08.080 align:middle line:90%
You simply say, OK.

00:34:08.080 --> 00:34:11.770 align:middle line:84%
I hear that I can't have it, but
I also hear that I can have it.

00:34:11.770 --> 00:34:14.699 align:middle line:90%
Both perspectives keep in mind.

00:34:14.699 --> 00:34:20.820 align:middle line:84%
And the old saying goes, you
feed the idea which feeds you,

00:34:20.820 --> 00:34:22.659 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:34:22.659 --> 00:34:24.480 align:middle line:84%
You don't feed the
guy that's trying

00:34:24.480 --> 00:34:28.409 align:middle line:84%
to defeat you, but feed the one
that's trying to support you.

00:34:28.409 --> 00:34:31.998 align:middle line:84%
So you go into the more positive
for yourself perspective.

00:34:31.998 --> 00:34:33.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what
visualization is.

00:34:33.540 --> 00:34:34.679 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: That's visualization.

00:34:34.679 --> 00:34:34.949 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:34:34.949 --> 00:34:35.749 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:34:35.749 --> 00:34:38.889 align:middle line:84%
And you have a way of breaking
it down on how this all works.

00:34:38.889 --> 00:34:40.500 align:middle line:84%
We have another
slide here where you

00:34:40.500 --> 00:34:45.210 align:middle line:84%
have how we construct
the past, the quantum.

00:34:45.210 --> 00:34:46.260 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Right.

00:34:46.260 --> 00:34:49.949 align:middle line:84%
Well, in this
particular slide, we

00:34:49.949 --> 00:34:53.389 align:middle line:84%
have a particle of
light, a photon.

00:34:53.389 --> 00:34:56.400 align:middle line:84%
And it enters what is called
a half silvered mirror.

00:34:56.400 --> 00:34:58.980 align:middle line:90%
It's coming in, say, like that.

00:34:58.980 --> 00:35:02.310 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is that
according to quantum physics,

00:35:02.310 --> 00:35:05.590 align:middle line:84%
it breaks up into
two possibilities.

00:35:05.590 --> 00:35:07.620 align:middle line:90%
I didn't say actualities.

00:35:07.620 --> 00:35:09.960 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't become two photons.

00:35:09.960 --> 00:35:14.820 align:middle line:84%
It's only two photon
ghost possibilities

00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:18.960 align:middle line:84%
that go on separate paths, and
then reflect off of mirrors

00:35:18.960 --> 00:35:21.090 align:middle line:90%
and come back together again.

00:35:21.090 --> 00:35:23.550 align:middle line:84%
And there's another
half silvered mirror

00:35:23.550 --> 00:35:26.880 align:middle line:90%
at the top of that diagram.

00:35:26.880 --> 00:35:31.020 align:middle line:84%
And if the two ghost
patterns are in phase

00:35:31.020 --> 00:35:33.450 align:middle line:84%
with each other, which
means they're vibratory

00:35:33.450 --> 00:35:39.060 align:middle line:84%
in the same way, then
those two ghost waves

00:35:39.060 --> 00:35:41.890 align:middle line:84%
will only reinforce
in one direction,

00:35:41.890 --> 00:35:47.400 align:middle line:84%
and you'll get a picture of
the photon, a pop appearing

00:35:47.400 --> 00:35:51.690 align:middle line:84%
in one of the collectors,
whereas if for some reason,

00:35:51.690 --> 00:35:53.430 align:middle line:84%
they're out of phase,
you can get one

00:35:53.430 --> 00:35:55.350 align:middle line:90%
popping or the other popping.

00:35:55.350 --> 00:35:56.682 align:middle line:90%
You get either one popping.

00:35:56.682 --> 00:35:59.140 align:middle line:84%
But if they're in phase, you
only get one of those popping.

00:35:59.140 --> 00:35:59.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:35:59.940 --> 00:36:06.307 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Now if you for
some reason take the--

00:36:06.307 --> 00:36:08.640 align:middle line:84%
remember that you have a
mirror which splits them apart.

00:36:08.640 --> 00:36:10.950 align:middle line:84%
Then you have a mirror that's
on top which joins them.

00:36:10.950 --> 00:36:18.060 align:middle line:84%
If you take that mirror out
and then you have the particle,

00:36:18.060 --> 00:36:21.690 align:middle line:84%
the ghost particles, which
so far, as far as you know,

00:36:21.690 --> 00:36:28.380 align:middle line:84%
are still on two possible
paths, yet either collector,

00:36:28.380 --> 00:36:33.960 align:middle line:84%
either observer, either one
of those collecting plates

00:36:33.960 --> 00:36:40.650 align:middle line:84%
or whatever you want to call
it will pop, but not both.

00:36:40.650 --> 00:36:42.580 align:middle line:90%
One or the other.

00:36:42.580 --> 00:36:44.520 align:middle line:84%
Now the question you
have in your mind

00:36:44.520 --> 00:36:47.760 align:middle line:84%
is given that one of
those or the other popped,

00:36:47.760 --> 00:36:52.020 align:middle line:84%
and there's no way to
add things together,

00:36:52.020 --> 00:36:54.990 align:middle line:84%
because there's no mirror
there to make that happen,

00:36:54.990 --> 00:36:59.070 align:middle line:84%
then you'd have to
say, well, how did that

00:36:59.070 --> 00:37:01.460 align:middle line:90%
mirror to the right pop?

00:37:01.460 --> 00:37:03.060 align:middle line:84%
The only way it
could have popped

00:37:03.060 --> 00:37:06.780 align:middle line:84%
is that the photon must
have only gone on one path.

00:37:06.780 --> 00:37:08.560 align:middle line:90%
It didn't split apart.

00:37:08.560 --> 00:37:11.500 align:middle line:84%
So it reflected, and
then went on one path.

00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:14.490 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand,
if I put the mirror in,

00:37:14.490 --> 00:37:16.260 align:middle line:90%
then it had to go on both paths.

00:37:16.260 --> 00:37:18.340 align:middle line:90%
So mirror in, it's both paths.

00:37:18.340 --> 00:37:20.800 align:middle line:84%
Mirror out, it's one
path or the other.

00:37:20.800 --> 00:37:24.090 align:middle line:84%
So now the question is,
the light enters the tube,

00:37:24.090 --> 00:37:26.280 align:middle line:84%
and let's imagine the
tube is very long.

00:37:26.280 --> 00:37:30.120 align:middle line:84%
Let's say that light is coming
from Alpha Centauri, 4.3

00:37:30.120 --> 00:37:31.590 align:middle line:90%
light years away, whatever.

00:37:31.590 --> 00:37:36.030 align:middle line:84%
And the two ghost paths are
around some star in between

00:37:36.030 --> 00:37:37.740 align:middle line:90%
or something, whatever.

00:37:37.740 --> 00:37:41.310 align:middle line:84%
Galaxy in between so that now we
have two possible ghost paths.

00:37:41.310 --> 00:37:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And so now it's been traveling
4.3 light years, 4.3 years

00:37:45.690 --> 00:37:47.280 align:middle line:90%
