00:39:25.250 --> 00:39:27.770 align:middle line:84%
hard work, hard
work, hard work--

00:39:27.770 --> 00:39:29.480 align:middle line:90%
puts you in a bind.

00:39:29.480 --> 00:39:31.800 align:middle line:90%
And that is your past.

00:39:31.800 --> 00:39:32.990 align:middle line:90%
That's what you see.

00:39:32.990 --> 00:39:36.260 align:middle line:84%
That's what you think
is your reality.

00:39:36.260 --> 00:39:38.330 align:middle line:84%
And anybody that tells
you that isn't true,

00:39:38.330 --> 00:39:42.620 align:middle line:84%
you think they're crazy,
they're misguided, whatever.

00:39:42.620 --> 00:39:46.970 align:middle line:84%
But the truth is, I got to
where I got to by my hard work.

00:39:46.970 --> 00:39:47.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:39:47.840 --> 00:39:50.032 align:middle line:84%
But you can look at it--
you can come at it from two

00:39:50.032 --> 00:39:50.990 align:middle line:90%
different perspectives.

00:39:50.990 --> 00:39:52.010 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Exactly.

00:39:52.010 --> 00:39:53.280 align:middle line:90%
And you create the past.

00:39:53.280 --> 00:39:54.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:39:54.080 --> 00:39:54.880 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:39:54.880 --> 00:39:56.600 align:middle line:84%
So along those
same lines, when we

00:39:56.600 --> 00:39:59.900 align:middle line:84%
are creating an image
of the past, what

00:39:59.900 --> 00:40:04.790 align:middle line:84%
happens when we're going into
the future and we have doubt,

00:40:04.790 --> 00:40:08.120 align:middle line:90%
we have worry, we have fear?

00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:09.320 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: OK.

00:40:09.320 --> 00:40:12.050 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at it from a point of
view of what we call a quantum

00:40:12.050 --> 00:40:14.540 align:middle line:90%
field idea, OK?

00:40:14.540 --> 00:40:18.680 align:middle line:84%
In the quantum
field theory, which

00:40:18.680 --> 00:40:22.310 align:middle line:84%
seems to be the best theory we
have going right now to explain

00:40:22.310 --> 00:40:29.510 align:middle line:84%
a lot of basic understanding
at the submicroscopic level,

00:40:29.510 --> 00:40:32.150 align:middle line:84%
there are fields,
quantum fields.

00:40:32.150 --> 00:40:35.330 align:middle line:84%
And what we call
events or particles

00:40:35.330 --> 00:40:38.840 align:middle line:84%
are things that
pop in the field.

00:40:38.840 --> 00:40:40.070 align:middle line:90%
They're like excitations.

00:40:40.070 --> 00:40:44.840 align:middle line:84%
They're like little bubbles of
froth on the ocean wave, OK?

00:40:44.840 --> 00:40:51.090 align:middle line:84%
And the picture we
have is that there

00:40:51.090 --> 00:40:57.800 align:middle line:84%
are, between any two events
separated in space or time,

00:40:57.800 --> 00:41:01.280 align:middle line:84%
there are multiple
paths connecting those.

00:41:01.280 --> 00:41:02.670 align:middle line:90%
Many ways of getting there.

00:41:02.670 --> 00:41:03.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:41:03.470 --> 00:41:04.280 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:41:04.280 --> 00:41:08.510 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So that's basically
the quantum field.

00:41:08.510 --> 00:41:15.040 align:middle line:84%
Now in terms of
our everyday life,

00:41:15.040 --> 00:41:19.670 align:middle line:84%
we have to understand that
both the past and the present

00:41:19.670 --> 00:41:22.310 align:middle line:84%
or the present
and the future are

00:41:22.310 --> 00:41:24.380 align:middle line:84%
from the point of
view of quantum fields

00:41:24.380 --> 00:41:25.275 align:middle line:90%
already in existence.

00:41:25.275 --> 00:41:26.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's fascinating.

00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:28.200 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: They're already there.

00:41:28.200 --> 00:41:29.970 align:middle line:90%
We're just finding out about it.

00:41:29.970 --> 00:41:33.410 align:middle line:84%
You've got to think of it as
time is like a river flowing.

00:41:33.410 --> 00:41:36.530 align:middle line:84%
And it's just flowing by,
flowing by, flowing by.

00:41:36.530 --> 00:41:42.885 align:middle line:84%
And we are in the river with
it, so we're flowing with it.

00:41:42.885 --> 00:41:44.720 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:41:44.720 --> 00:41:47.960 align:middle line:84%
But if we get out of the
river and stand on the shore,

00:41:47.960 --> 00:41:50.880 align:middle line:84%
we can look ahead and see
where the river's going to be.

00:41:50.880 --> 00:41:52.790 align:middle line:90%
We can see where the river was.

00:41:52.790 --> 00:41:54.422 align:middle line:90%
We can see both the past and--

00:41:54.422 --> 00:41:56.630 align:middle line:84%
the quantum field point of
view is being on the side,

00:41:56.630 --> 00:41:58.940 align:middle line:84%
looking at the
past and the future

00:41:58.940 --> 00:42:00.390 align:middle line:90%
of the river at the same time.

00:42:00.390 --> 00:42:01.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:42:01.190 --> 00:42:01.990 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: OK?

00:42:01.990 --> 00:42:03.810 align:middle line:90%
So that's the perspective.

00:42:03.810 --> 00:42:09.320 align:middle line:84%
Now what happens is that when
there is an idea, desire,

00:42:09.320 --> 00:42:13.850 align:middle line:84%
something that you want that
connects these two events,

00:42:13.850 --> 00:42:17.960 align:middle line:84%
then what happens is that not
only is there something which

00:42:17.960 --> 00:42:21.830 align:middle line:84%
travels forward from your
point of view through time,

00:42:21.830 --> 00:42:24.720 align:middle line:84%
but there's also something
which comes back.

00:42:24.720 --> 00:42:27.798 align:middle line:84%
So if you have the thought,
I want to make this happen,

00:42:27.798 --> 00:42:30.090 align:middle line:84%
I believe this is good,
there's also the thought, well,

00:42:30.090 --> 00:42:32.810 align:middle line:90%
what if you don't do it right?

00:42:32.810 --> 00:42:37.010 align:middle line:84%
So doubt is also a message
that you can receive,

00:42:37.010 --> 00:42:39.238 align:middle line:84%
because the movement
is both ways.

00:42:39.238 --> 00:42:40.280 align:middle line:90%
You can look to the past.

00:42:40.280 --> 00:42:41.550 align:middle line:90%
You can look to the--

00:42:41.550 --> 00:42:42.440 align:middle line:90%
you can see both.

00:42:42.440 --> 00:42:44.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's how we
create our reality.

00:42:44.880 --> 00:42:48.020 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So our realities
come into vision that way.

00:42:48.020 --> 00:42:50.970 align:middle line:84%
Now we can also do it
the other way around.

00:42:50.970 --> 00:42:54.350 align:middle line:84%
We may have the vision of
focusing, oh, we can't do that.

00:42:54.350 --> 00:42:57.980 align:middle line:84%
But then it comes back in
message, oh, yes, you can.

00:42:57.980 --> 00:43:02.060 align:middle line:84%
So doubt is always
going to be present.

00:43:02.060 --> 00:43:04.520 align:middle line:90%
Doubt is part of the parcel.

00:43:04.520 --> 00:43:05.600 align:middle line:90%
It's part of a picture.

00:43:05.600 --> 00:43:07.630 align:middle line:84%
It's part of the
whole bag of tricks

00:43:07.630 --> 00:43:08.940 align:middle line:90%
that we have to deal with.

00:43:08.940 --> 00:43:12.320 align:middle line:84%
And it's a question of,
let it be, because it's

00:43:12.320 --> 00:43:13.520 align:middle line:90%
healthy to have doubt.

00:43:13.520 --> 00:43:16.780 align:middle line:84%
But if you go with the
doubt, you never do anything.

00:43:16.780 --> 00:43:17.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:43:17.580 --> 00:43:18.380 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:43:18.380 --> 00:43:21.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for fatalistic thinking
and people that really always

00:43:21.590 --> 00:43:23.630 align:middle line:84%
look at the worst
case scenario, they're

00:43:23.630 --> 00:43:25.880 align:middle line:84%
going to create that,
because they never

00:43:25.880 --> 00:43:30.320 align:middle line:84%
have the opposite strain
or string that comes in.

00:43:30.320 --> 00:43:31.660 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: They stay always--

00:43:31.660 --> 00:43:34.100 align:middle line:84%
they're in the
skeptical land view.

00:43:34.100 --> 00:43:36.860 align:middle line:90%
In the skeptical land view--

00:43:36.860 --> 00:43:39.890 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how to
put their perspective--

00:43:39.890 --> 00:43:42.130 align:middle line:84%
they're kind of
caught in the stream.

00:43:42.130 --> 00:43:43.170 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:43:43.170 --> 00:43:43.970 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:43:43.970 --> 00:43:44.905 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:43:44.905 --> 00:43:46.280 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I know
someone like this,

00:43:46.280 --> 00:43:48.710 align:middle line:84%
and they constantly create
the worst case scenario.

00:43:48.710 --> 00:43:49.610 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: The worse case scenario.

00:43:49.610 --> 00:43:50.300 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:43:50.300 --> 00:43:51.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Constantly.

00:43:51.100 --> 00:43:52.550 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So they're
always thinking

00:43:52.550 --> 00:43:55.310 align:middle line:84%
about what bad things are
going to happen to them.

00:43:55.310 --> 00:43:58.232 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it always happens,
because when I say, why do you

00:43:58.232 --> 00:44:00.440 align:middle line:84%
always go to the worst case
scenario, they say, well,

00:44:00.440 --> 00:44:01.130 align:middle line:90%
you've got to be aware.

00:44:01.130 --> 00:44:02.160 align:middle line:90%
You've got to understand.

00:44:02.160 --> 00:44:04.230 align:middle line:84%
You've got to know that these
things are going to happen.

00:44:04.230 --> 00:44:05.647 align:middle line:84%
But what you're
saying is, there's

00:44:05.647 --> 00:44:07.950 align:middle line:84%
another reality
that can come in.

00:44:07.950 --> 00:44:11.150 align:middle line:84%
It's good to be aware, but
enter in this reality of--

00:44:11.150 --> 00:44:13.110 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: There's also the
opposite of the doubt.

00:44:13.110 --> 00:44:13.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:44:13.910 --> 00:44:17.270 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So whatever you're
doubting, turn it upside down

00:44:17.270 --> 00:44:21.110 align:middle line:84%
or around and see, what
is it that could happen

00:44:21.110 --> 00:44:23.640 align:middle line:90%
that is not within the doubt?

00:44:23.640 --> 00:44:24.440 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it is.

00:44:24.440 --> 00:44:25.487 align:middle line:90%
Whatever you're doubting.

00:44:25.487 --> 00:44:27.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Byron Katie's
"The Work" I think of.

00:44:27.320 --> 00:44:28.880 align:middle line:90%
She has this turnaround.

00:44:28.880 --> 00:44:30.720 align:middle line:90%
So what if it wasn't that way?

00:44:30.720 --> 00:44:31.520 align:middle line:90%
How would it be?

00:44:31.520 --> 00:44:33.590 align:middle line:84%
And this is a great
thing for visualization,

00:44:33.590 --> 00:44:37.196 align:middle line:84%
to see things the way
you want them to be.

00:44:37.196 --> 00:44:39.890 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: It's seeing things
the way you want them to be.

00:44:39.890 --> 00:44:42.440 align:middle line:84%
And there's another very
important part of this.

00:44:42.440 --> 00:44:45.230 align:middle line:90%
We're in material form.

00:44:45.230 --> 00:44:47.420 align:middle line:84%
We're not just
pixelated dots, even

00:44:47.420 --> 00:44:51.470 align:middle line:84%
though that's what we're
coming to in virtual reality.

00:44:51.470 --> 00:44:53.710 align:middle line:90%
But we have to get up and move.

00:44:53.710 --> 00:44:54.510 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:44:54.510 --> 00:44:55.520 align:middle line:90%


00:44:55.520 --> 00:44:58.190 align:middle line:84%
Once we have the picture,
let's do something about it.

00:44:58.190 --> 00:45:02.300 align:middle line:84%
Let's not just sit there
and hope for the best.

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:05.270 align:middle line:84%
Move along the path
which takes you there.

00:45:05.270 --> 00:45:08.060 align:middle line:90%
Walk your talk, so to speak.

00:45:08.060 --> 00:45:11.465 align:middle line:84%
Move along the path
which takes you there.

00:45:11.465 --> 00:45:13.940 align:middle line:84%
You can also move along
the path which you doubt.

00:45:13.940 --> 00:45:15.440 align:middle line:84%
I doubt it's going
to happen, so I'm

00:45:15.440 --> 00:45:18.420 align:middle line:84%
going to do everything I can to
make sure that doesn't happen.

00:45:18.420 --> 00:45:19.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:19.220 --> 00:45:21.317 align:middle line:84%
That's the difference
between how and who.

00:45:21.317 --> 00:45:23.150 align:middle line:84%
I've heard it said,
well, how do we do this?

00:45:23.150 --> 00:45:24.020 align:middle line:90%
How do we do this?

00:45:24.020 --> 00:45:27.000 align:middle line:84%
Instead of moving into,
who can help us do this?

00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:27.800 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:45:27.800 --> 00:45:31.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It takes the how
of the idea of the quantum,

00:45:31.370 --> 00:45:33.830 align:middle line:84%
and then it brings in
the action piece which

00:45:33.830 --> 00:45:36.490 align:middle line:84%
is, who can actually help
you do something or help you?

00:45:36.490 --> 00:45:37.290 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:45:37.290 --> 00:45:38.220 align:middle line:10%
Yes.

00:45:38.220 --> 00:45:39.020 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:45:39.020 --> 00:45:40.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So this is a
great conversation,

00:45:40.790 --> 00:45:43.520 align:middle line:84%
because we're talking about
everything from quantum fields,

00:45:43.520 --> 00:45:47.100 align:middle line:84%
parallel reality, string theory,
essentially, entanglement,

00:45:47.100 --> 00:45:47.900 align:middle line:90%
everything.

00:45:47.900 --> 00:45:48.410 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:45:48.410 --> 00:45:49.360 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: We haven't
got to strings yet.

00:45:49.360 --> 00:45:50.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, we haven't--

00:45:50.640 --> 00:45:52.266 align:middle line:90%
we're talking about different--

00:45:52.266 --> 00:45:54.170 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Talking about
the quantum fields.

00:45:54.170 --> 00:45:54.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:45:54.970 --> 00:45:59.500 align:middle line:84%
So now in the quantum field,
you can recreate your past,

00:45:59.500 --> 00:46:02.860 align:middle line:84%
essentially, by changing
your perspective

00:46:02.860 --> 00:46:05.755 align:middle line:90%
on where the river has gone.

00:46:05.755 --> 00:46:08.350 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: In order to
do that, you have

00:46:08.350 --> 00:46:10.780 align:middle line:84%
to come out of the
river, so to speak,

00:46:10.780 --> 00:46:12.670 align:middle line:90%
and be able to look back.

00:46:12.670 --> 00:46:16.460 align:middle line:84%
And it's a question of how
you do that looking back.

00:46:16.460 --> 00:46:17.615 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:46:17.615 --> 00:46:19.870 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: In other words,
the river's flowing.

00:46:19.870 --> 00:46:22.330 align:middle line:84%
So whenever you're
looking back, the past

00:46:22.330 --> 00:46:24.233 align:middle line:84%
is constantly being
recreated all the time,

00:46:24.233 --> 00:46:25.400 align:middle line:90%
because the river's flowing.

00:46:25.400 --> 00:46:26.080 align:middle line:90%
It's flowing.

00:46:26.080 --> 00:46:26.620 align:middle line:90%
It's flowing.

00:46:26.620 --> 00:46:27.290 align:middle line:90%
What's back there?

00:46:27.290 --> 00:46:28.030 align:middle line:90%
Oh, what's back there?

00:46:28.030 --> 00:46:28.780 align:middle line:90%
What's back there?

00:46:28.780 --> 00:46:29.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:46:29.580 --> 00:46:30.400 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:46:30.400 --> 00:46:32.898 align:middle line:84%
Now how does string
theory relate to anything

00:46:32.898 --> 00:46:33.940 align:middle line:90%
that we're talking about?

00:46:33.940 --> 00:46:34.740 align:middle line:90%
I know that's not--

00:46:34.740 --> 00:46:36.010 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:46:36.010 --> 00:46:37.250 align:middle line:90%
--a slide.

00:46:37.250 --> 00:46:42.790 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, it is
the, I would say,

00:46:42.790 --> 00:46:47.920 align:middle line:84%
the last vestige of
the mechanical world

00:46:47.920 --> 00:46:53.470 align:middle line:84%
view that we physicists
in particular

00:46:53.470 --> 00:46:56.660 align:middle line:90%
are trying to develop.

00:46:56.660 --> 00:47:00.310 align:middle line:84%
The one thing about everything
we've talked about so far

00:47:00.310 --> 00:47:03.280 align:middle line:84%
is we've left off the
most common thing we all

00:47:03.280 --> 00:47:05.920 align:middle line:90%
experience called gravity.

00:47:05.920 --> 00:47:09.320 align:middle line:84%
And when you try to put gravity
and quantum physics together,

00:47:09.320 --> 00:47:10.600 align:middle line:90%
it becomes a mess.

00:47:10.600 --> 00:47:13.030 align:middle line:90%
They don't jive.

00:47:13.030 --> 00:47:16.450 align:middle line:84%
They don't work quite
together the right way.

00:47:16.450 --> 00:47:18.580 align:middle line:84%
People have been modeling
that with all kinds

00:47:18.580 --> 00:47:22.820 align:middle line:84%
of interesting ideas, and
some of them are fascinating.

00:47:22.820 --> 00:47:27.260 align:middle line:84%
But the one that started
developing about 30,

00:47:27.260 --> 00:47:28.310 align:middle line:90%
40, 50 years ago--

00:47:28.310 --> 00:47:29.610 align:middle line:90%
I'm not sure exactly when--

00:47:29.610 --> 00:47:31.152 align:middle line:84%
something called
string theory, which

00:47:31.152 --> 00:47:34.120 align:middle line:84%
said that there are
not point particles.

00:47:34.120 --> 00:47:36.380 align:middle line:90%
There are strings.

00:47:36.380 --> 00:47:39.310 align:middle line:84%
Each so-called particle
is made of strings.

00:47:39.310 --> 00:47:44.140 align:middle line:84%
And these are not just-- they're
vibrating energy strings.

00:47:44.140 --> 00:47:46.090 align:middle line:90%
So they're energy vibrations.

00:47:46.090 --> 00:47:48.220 align:middle line:90%
So in a way, it's not particle.

00:47:48.220 --> 00:47:49.940 align:middle line:90%
It's energy vibrations.

00:47:49.940 --> 00:47:53.290 align:middle line:84%
But Einstein says
e equal mc squared,

00:47:53.290 --> 00:47:55.880 align:middle line:84%
so energy and
matter are the same.

00:47:55.880 --> 00:47:59.090 align:middle line:84%
So if energy is there, there's
got to be matter there,

00:47:59.090 --> 00:48:00.230 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:48:00.230 --> 00:48:03.550 align:middle line:84%
So that's the basis
of string theory.

00:48:03.550 --> 00:48:04.990 align:middle line:90%
It's very complicated.

00:48:04.990 --> 00:48:06.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:48:06.140 --> 00:48:07.450 align:middle line:90%
It's a great, great example.

00:48:07.450 --> 00:48:07.840 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:48:07.840 --> 00:48:08.640 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:48:08.640 --> 00:48:12.730 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've given you just
the real basic aspect of it.

00:48:12.730 --> 00:48:14.980 align:middle line:84%
And there are some interesting
things that come about.

00:48:14.980 --> 00:48:18.010 align:middle line:84%
I mean, such that gravity
can be incorporated.

00:48:18.010 --> 00:48:22.330 align:middle line:84%
But it requires
extra dimensions.

00:48:22.330 --> 00:48:24.590 align:middle line:90%
I think 11, 12, 17.

