00:49:53.110 --> 00:49:54.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What are
your interests now?

00:49:54.660 --> 00:49:56.678 align:middle line:90%
What are you moving into?

00:49:56.678 --> 00:49:57.970 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: That's a good question.

00:49:57.970 --> 00:49:58.770 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:49:58.770 --> 00:49:59.570 align:middle line:90%


00:49:59.570 --> 00:50:02.140 align:middle line:84%
What I'm interested in right
now is something called context

00:50:02.140 --> 00:50:04.930 align:middle line:90%
duality.

00:50:04.930 --> 00:50:12.600 align:middle line:84%
The question is, is what we
observed, what we observe,

00:50:12.600 --> 00:50:17.430 align:middle line:84%
affected by the background
in which it is observed?

00:50:17.430 --> 00:50:21.120 align:middle line:84%
In other words, is
there an objective--

00:50:21.120 --> 00:50:23.130 align:middle line:84%
if I observe something
one way, is it always

00:50:23.130 --> 00:50:24.750 align:middle line:90%
going to be that way?

00:50:24.750 --> 00:50:29.370 align:middle line:84%
Or does my observation depend
upon what others have observed?

00:50:29.370 --> 00:50:31.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So say we're
looking at this cup.

00:50:31.120 --> 00:50:31.920 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:50:31.920 --> 00:50:35.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And we want
to observe this cup.

00:50:35.400 --> 00:50:38.580 align:middle line:84%
You're talking about
the field around it?

00:50:38.580 --> 00:50:42.210 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: The table, the
flowers, everything around it.

00:50:42.210 --> 00:50:47.550 align:middle line:84%
The question is, if I observe
the cup and I only see the cup,

00:50:47.550 --> 00:50:51.510 align:middle line:84%
is what I see of the cup going
to change depending upon what

00:50:51.510 --> 00:50:53.620 align:middle line:90%
environment that cup is in?

00:50:53.620 --> 00:50:54.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:50:54.420 --> 00:50:55.220 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:50:55.220 --> 00:50:58.080 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And so the whole
idea of contextual--

00:50:58.080 --> 00:51:02.370 align:middle line:84%
we used to think that in
so-called classical physics

00:51:02.370 --> 00:51:06.660 align:middle line:90%
that things were non-contextual.

00:51:06.660 --> 00:51:09.010 align:middle line:84%
A ball is a ball is
a ball is a ball.

00:51:09.010 --> 00:51:11.060 align:middle line:90%
Red is red is red.

00:51:11.060 --> 00:51:12.140 align:middle line:90%
Non-contextual.

00:51:12.140 --> 00:51:14.880 align:middle line:84%
It didn't matter what
other colors were there,

00:51:14.880 --> 00:51:19.200 align:middle line:84%
but we all sort of learned
that even observation of color

00:51:19.200 --> 00:51:20.820 align:middle line:90%
changes depending on background.

00:51:20.820 --> 00:51:21.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Amazing.

00:51:21.620 --> 00:51:23.490 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So obviously,
contextuality

00:51:23.490 --> 00:51:27.580 align:middle line:84%
does affect what
we call reality.

00:51:27.580 --> 00:51:30.840 align:middle line:84%
So the context duality
of political thinking

00:51:30.840 --> 00:51:34.620 align:middle line:90%
affects how we think today.

00:51:34.620 --> 00:51:37.410 align:middle line:84%
So all these things
are based upon what

00:51:37.410 --> 00:51:39.450 align:middle line:90%
I call context duality.

00:51:39.450 --> 00:51:43.470 align:middle line:84%
So my interest has been in,
how to explain context duality?

00:51:43.470 --> 00:51:45.780 align:middle line:84%
The other things which
interests me is, how do we

00:51:45.780 --> 00:51:47.820 align:middle line:90%
explain how do we explain?

00:51:47.820 --> 00:51:48.702 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wait, wait.

00:51:48.702 --> 00:51:49.910 align:middle line:90%
I want to go there for a sec.

00:51:49.910 --> 00:51:51.410 align:middle line:84%
But what you were
just talking about

00:51:51.410 --> 00:51:53.215 align:middle line:84%
is along the lines
of epigenetics, yes?

00:51:53.215 --> 00:51:54.090 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: I don't know.

00:51:54.090 --> 00:51:55.440 align:middle line:90%
What is epigemetics?

00:51:55.440 --> 00:51:56.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Epigenetics.

00:51:56.280 --> 00:51:56.880 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:51:56.880 --> 00:51:57.370 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: What is it?

00:51:57.370 --> 00:51:58.380 align:middle line:90%
I'm not sure what it is.

00:51:58.380 --> 00:52:02.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's where the
environment creates the--

00:52:02.070 --> 00:52:06.630 align:middle line:84%
it affects the cells or
what's happening in the body.

00:52:06.630 --> 00:52:08.610 align:middle line:90%
So you can actually be--

00:52:08.610 --> 00:52:10.460 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Well, that's part of it.

00:52:10.460 --> 00:52:11.260 align:middle line:90%
That's part of it.

00:52:11.260 --> 00:52:14.520 align:middle line:84%
But we're more dealing
here with observation.

00:52:14.520 --> 00:52:18.210 align:middle line:84%
In other words,
is what I observe

00:52:18.210 --> 00:52:21.330 align:middle line:90%
of something going to change--

00:52:21.330 --> 00:52:24.210 align:middle line:84%
if I keep observing exactly
the same way all the time,

00:52:24.210 --> 00:52:26.780 align:middle line:84%
but put it in a different
context, will it change?

00:52:26.780 --> 00:52:30.030 align:middle line:84%
And the answer seems to be
under certain cin-- circun--

00:52:30.030 --> 00:52:30.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Stances.

00:52:30.830 --> 00:52:34.110 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: --certain circumstances
it will actually change.

00:52:34.110 --> 00:52:36.200 align:middle line:90%
And so there's a context--

00:52:36.200 --> 00:52:39.420 align:middle line:84%
quantum physics is indicated,
there is definitely

00:52:39.420 --> 00:52:42.090 align:middle line:90%
a contextual aspect to it.

00:52:42.090 --> 00:52:46.020 align:middle line:84%
What this is leading
to is that the world

00:52:46.020 --> 00:52:51.060 align:middle line:90%
is more mental than physical.

00:52:51.060 --> 00:52:53.100 align:middle line:84%
There's more of a
mental aspect to it.

00:52:53.100 --> 00:52:56.075 align:middle line:90%


00:52:56.075 --> 00:52:58.240 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I think
this is leading to.

00:52:58.240 --> 00:53:00.690 align:middle line:84%
So that's kind of the
direction I've gotten into.

00:53:00.690 --> 00:53:04.380 align:middle line:84%
And you asked me
what my interest was.

00:53:04.380 --> 00:53:08.730 align:middle line:84%
Along with that are questions
that come up in subjects

00:53:08.730 --> 00:53:12.060 align:middle line:84%
we call ontology
and epistemology.

00:53:12.060 --> 00:53:15.600 align:middle line:84%
Ontology is, what's
really out there?

00:53:15.600 --> 00:53:18.610 align:middle line:84%
Epistemology is, what do we
think is really out there?

00:53:18.610 --> 00:53:19.410 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:53:19.410 --> 00:53:22.050 align:middle line:84%
So there's two different
ways of thinking.

00:53:22.050 --> 00:53:25.050 align:middle line:84%
Quantum physics has taken
epistemology and ontology,

00:53:25.050 --> 00:53:28.980 align:middle line:84%
which were quite well separated
in most people's minds,

00:53:28.980 --> 00:53:32.190 align:middle line:84%
and jumbled them up
into kind of an omelet.

00:53:32.190 --> 00:53:32.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:53:32.990 --> 00:53:33.790 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:53:33.790 --> 00:53:35.340 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: One, physicist
Julian Jaynes,

00:53:35.340 --> 00:53:38.500 align:middle line:90%
made that picture of that.

00:53:38.500 --> 00:53:45.120 align:middle line:84%
So we can no longer say that
what we think about and--

00:53:45.120 --> 00:53:47.320 align:middle line:84%
what we think is really
there and what is really

00:53:47.320 --> 00:53:50.100 align:middle line:84%
there are really things
that can be separated.

00:53:50.100 --> 00:53:52.350 align:middle line:90%
They're no longer separable.

00:53:52.350 --> 00:53:54.880 align:middle line:84%
And this is what quantum physics
has brought into picture.

00:53:54.880 --> 00:53:58.510 align:middle line:84%
So this led me to thinking
about a lot of different things.

00:53:58.510 --> 00:54:04.260 align:middle line:84%
There is a school of thought
that a German mathematician

00:54:04.260 --> 00:54:06.800 align:middle line:84%
who spent a lot of time
with Einstein at Princeton--

00:54:06.800 --> 00:54:13.290 align:middle line:84%
Kurt Godel-- G-O-D-E-L, with an
umlaut over the O, Kurt Godel--

00:54:13.290 --> 00:54:19.000 align:middle line:84%
he came up with the
principle of undecidability.

00:54:19.000 --> 00:54:23.140 align:middle line:84%
And he said that a system
even like arithmetic,

00:54:23.140 --> 00:54:26.670 align:middle line:84%
which everybody understands,
it's possible to make

00:54:26.670 --> 00:54:31.410 align:middle line:84%
statements about arithmetic
which cannot be proven under

00:54:31.410 --> 00:54:33.390 align:middle line:90%
the laws of arithmetic.

00:54:33.390 --> 00:54:35.130 align:middle line:90%
They're undecidable.

00:54:35.130 --> 00:54:37.860 align:middle line:84%
They seem to be
true, but we can't

00:54:37.860 --> 00:54:40.240 align:middle line:90%
prove by the principles of--

00:54:40.240 --> 00:54:41.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:54:41.040 --> 00:54:41.870 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: I mean, for
example, there's

00:54:41.870 --> 00:54:43.260 align:middle line:90%
some things we can easily prove.

00:54:43.260 --> 00:54:44.280 align:middle line:90%
2 plus 2 is 4.

00:54:44.280 --> 00:54:46.050 align:middle line:90%
We can easily prove that.

00:54:46.050 --> 00:54:50.520 align:middle line:84%
That's within the
principles of arithmetic.

00:54:50.520 --> 00:54:53.395 align:middle line:84%
But there are other principles
which we cannot prove.

00:54:53.395 --> 00:54:54.270 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to get--

00:54:54.270 --> 00:54:56.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: As you get more into
mathematics and deeper into it.

00:54:56.490 --> 00:54:58.170 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Gets more into
logic of mathematics.

00:54:58.170 --> 00:54:58.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Logic, yes.

00:54:58.970 --> 00:55:02.630 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And so then it got me
thinking about, well, we're

00:55:02.630 --> 00:55:03.540 align:middle line:90%
into quantum physics.

00:55:03.540 --> 00:55:05.220 align:middle line:84%
Is it possible that
quantum physics

00:55:05.220 --> 00:55:09.270 align:middle line:84%
is itself capable of producing
statements about itself which

00:55:09.270 --> 00:55:10.620 align:middle line:90%
are unprovable?

00:55:10.620 --> 00:55:11.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of course.

00:55:11.780 --> 00:55:14.110 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So if that's
the case, then we're

00:55:14.110 --> 00:55:15.710 align:middle line:90%
really into a mental world.

00:55:15.710 --> 00:55:16.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:55:16.510 --> 00:55:18.400 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: The world cannot
be-- fundamentally,

00:55:18.400 --> 00:55:19.790 align:middle line:90%
it cannot be physical.

00:55:19.790 --> 00:55:20.680 align:middle line:90%
It has to be mental.

00:55:20.680 --> 00:55:21.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I mean,
it's interesting.

00:55:21.470 --> 00:55:23.512 align:middle line:84%
You apply what you're
talking about to everything

00:55:23.512 --> 00:55:25.325 align:middle line:84%
from fake news to
propaganda to fear.

00:55:25.325 --> 00:55:26.950 align:middle line:84%
And you can really
look at that and you

00:55:26.950 --> 00:55:29.410 align:middle line:84%
could say, what is
reality, and what is not?

00:55:29.410 --> 00:55:33.130 align:middle line:84%
And how much are we being
involved with the context of it

00:55:33.130 --> 00:55:36.400 align:middle line:84%
and impacted by the context
of it and what is real?

00:55:36.400 --> 00:55:38.910 align:middle line:84%
And I think that is happening
in our society today.

00:55:38.910 --> 00:55:41.800 align:middle line:84%
We really need to more
than ever determine

00:55:41.800 --> 00:55:44.990 align:middle line:84%
our own truth, which is why
this show is so important.

00:55:44.990 --> 00:55:45.790 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:55:45.790 --> 00:55:47.260 align:middle line:90%
I think it's really important.

00:55:47.260 --> 00:55:50.350 align:middle line:84%
I have to ask you, what
