00:59:12.010 --> 00:59:16.600 align:middle line:84%
Ask yourself the question,
who is observing?

00:59:16.600 --> 00:59:18.100 align:middle line:90%
Just ask.

00:59:18.100 --> 00:59:19.520 align:middle line:90%
Don't answer.

00:59:19.520 --> 00:59:20.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:59:20.320 --> 00:59:22.920 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: If you
answer, you get caught

00:59:22.920 --> 00:59:26.650 align:middle line:84%
in a framework in which
you define the relationship

00:59:26.650 --> 00:59:27.640 align:middle line:90%
in which you are in.

00:59:27.640 --> 00:59:28.682 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's important.

00:59:28.682 --> 00:59:32.740 align:middle line:84%
So if I am relating to my
daughter, I just say, I am--

00:59:32.740 --> 00:59:34.780 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Don't even ask--

00:59:34.780 --> 00:59:37.600 align:middle line:84%
just say, who is with
this other person?

00:59:37.600 --> 00:59:40.060 align:middle line:84%
Don't even think of the
other person as daughter.

00:59:40.060 --> 00:59:42.360 align:middle line:90%
Don't label the other person.

00:59:42.360 --> 00:59:45.940 align:middle line:84%
Just-- there's
another being there.

00:59:45.940 --> 00:59:47.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Who am I?

00:59:47.430 --> 00:59:48.230 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: What am I?

00:59:48.230 --> 00:59:49.030 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:59:49.030 --> 00:59:50.020 align:middle line:90%
Don't answer.

00:59:50.020 --> 00:59:53.680 align:middle line:84%
Just be with the person
without labeling yourself.

00:59:53.680 --> 00:59:55.600 align:middle line:84%
The other person might
get uncomfortable

00:59:55.600 --> 00:59:56.480 align:middle line:90%
